When Humpbacks are side lunging or skimming they are most likely eating krill, which is a crustacean shrimp-looking creature. Today we saw one of out first vertical lunge feeding of the year, which means that sardines and anchovies are coming back to the bay just in time for the hungry Humpback's Summer banquets!
